# ACT II — "The Book and the Wall"  (Candlekeep → the Fugue / City of Judgment)
# Find the truth of the Crown, then descend, alive, into the afterlife. Scholarly mystery to cosmic vertigo.
class: ActTwoMainContent

# ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
conversation: act2.candlekeep.gate | Act II — The Price of Entry
node: 0 | Gatewarden Khelben's Heir
  *(The doors of Candlekeep are taller than the church you were sealed under. The Gatewarden does not look up from her ledger.)* The toll is not coin. It never was. One book the library does not hold — yours to give, ours to keep, forever. That is the price of every page behind me. *(Now she looks up.)* You have the smell of someone who's read a page they shouldn't have. The Wall's page. So. What do you bring that ten thousand years of scholars did not?
  enter: SET act2.candlekeep_gate
  auto: 1
node: 1 | Gatewarden Khelben's Heir
  Choose carefully. We have heard every lie a desperate traveler can carry, and the Wall behind your eyes does not buy you mercy here. It buys you scrutiny.
  * [HISTORY 16] "A firsthand account of the Wall of the Faithless, dictated by a soul that walked out of it." -> firsthand ?? rejected
  * "Sister Garrow's funeral rites — forty years of the dead, named, that the church wanted forgotten." -> garrow_book | fx appr.garrow +6, SET act2.garrow_gave_book
  * [PERSUADE 17] "The book you don't have is the one I haven't written yet — my own. Let me in and it ends here, on your shelves." -> wager ?? rejected
  * "I'll find another way in." -> refuse
node: firsthand | Gatewarden Khelben's Heir
  *(For the first time in what is plainly a very long career, the Gatewarden sets down her pen.)* ...A primary source on the Faithless. From the inside. *(She is already gesturing the doors open, hungry as any scholar.)* No one has ever brought us *that*. Go down to the Sealed Stacks. What you seek about the Crown is there — and gods keep you, so is what you are. We have wondered, here, for an age. You may be the footnote that rewrites the spine.
  enter: SET act2.candlekeep_entered, SET act2.entry_firsthand
  auto: stacks
node: garrow_book | Gatewarden Khelben's Heir
